    more: "Money is the most liquid asset — it is already cash. Checking accounts are highly liquid. Savings accounts, money market funds, and short-term government bonds are near-liquid. Real estate and long-term bonds are illiquid. Investors typically demand a liquidity premium — a higher return — to hold less liquid assets.",
